<item>
            <title>[LU-13320] add io500.sh test script</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13320</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be very useful to add an &lt;tt&gt;io500.sh&lt;/tt&gt; test session that runs the &lt;tt&gt;io500&lt;/tt&gt; test on the current filesystem config using all of the clients configured.   This test session should take about 1h to run using the default test parameters.  It &lt;em&gt;does&lt;/em&gt; need working MPI on the clients in order to run, but I think that is true of other test sessions as well (e.g. &lt;tt&gt;sanity-benchmark&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would allow the benchmark to be run on a patch like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Test-Parameters: testlist=io500 [other options]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;on a patch to determine the performance impact of particular patches and to ensure that the test keeps working properly. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
